text: Honored to serve as co-chair of the 2018 National Prayer Breakfast. Tune in via @cspan 2 starting at 8am.
#OTD in 1940, the very first #SocialSecurity check was issued. Since then, it has helped lift millions out of poverty and improved the lives of our seniors.

Deeply disturbed by accounts of the President’s remarks on Haiti & Africa. Undignified behavior and embarrassing. In Florida, we have a vibrant Haitian community and people from every African nation. Disparaging them is hurtful, unfounded, and beneath the office of the President.
Tomorrow marks 5 years since Sandy Hook tragedy. Time for Congress to #HonorWithAction by passing common-sense gun violence prevention legislation.
One death is too many, 25 is horrifying. Today on Transgender Day of Remembrance we remember every #transgender life lost this year. #TDOR

This #VeteransDay we must also recognize our #HiddenHeroes who share in service and sacrifice, caring for the needs of our veterans. To our military families & caregivers – a grateful nation thanks you!
$196k #LWCF grant coming to #FL13 for 46th Ave. Rec. Trail construction. Congress must act before critical program disappears! #SaveLWCF
Fighting to #SaveLWCF that for 52yrs has protected places like Egmont Key & Skyway Fishing Pier in #FL13 before it expires in 52 weeks.
3.6million American citizens in #PuertoRico are fighting to recover. We must deploy every resource needed for relief for #OurFellowAmericans
As #OurFellowAmericans, #PuertoRico & #USVI need our nation’s united support to overcome the devastation from #HurricaneMaria.
Contradicting 20yrs of precedent, AG Sessions rolls back protections for #transgender workers. #Unbelievable RT to #protecttransworkers
My heart aches for all of the victims of the tragic massacre in Las Vegas. This is senseless, unimaginable. God bless our first responders.
September is ending but let’s make #suicidepreventionmonth every month, pledging to #BeThere for those who fought for us year-round.
My thoughts to everyone observing #YomKippur. Hope you have a meaningful day and easy fast.

Insurance = 1st line of defense against damage. NFIP policyholder? Contact your agent or call 800-621-3362 for more info on your coverage.

Hosting a Disaster Recovery 101 event TOMORROW at 1pm at the Clearwater Fire Station (1140 Court Street).
.@MyFDOT  announced that I-75 will remain open, as flood waters have been receding on the Santa Fe River.
The IRS automatically IDs taxpayers located in the covered disaster area (Pinellas) and applies automatic filing & payment relief. @IRSnews
.@FirstData is providing payment devices to impacted FL business owners, along with 80 field reps. Call 844-882-2438 for assistance.
Pinellas Econ Dev office staff available Wed (9/13) for biz disaster loan support if suffered physical damage from Irma. Call (727) 453-7200
.@Delta travel change, baggage, & pets in cabin fees waived for flights to/from hurricane-affected areas through 9/20. To SFl capped at $399
.@AmericanAir fares capped @ $99/$199 for Main/Prem cabin on direct flights to/from all cities covered under travel alert in FL through 9/17
.@FrontierCorp customers do not need to report service issues until power is restored. When power is restored, service should resume.
.@StateDept Embassies in Cuba, Haiti, and Dominican Republic open for limited services. Bahamas Embassy only open for emergency services.
From @StateDept: Urging US Citizens in  impacted areas who are safe to contact loved ones directly and update their social media status.

Pinellas biz are eligible for Physical & Economic Injury Disaster Loans from @SBAgov. Call 800-659-2955 or disastercustomerservice@sba.gov.
Per @StateDept: U.S. Embassy in Cuba suffered flood damage, do not attempt to travel to it. Contact by telephone at +53 5280-5791.
If you contacted @StateDept about help after Irma for you or a loved one & are now home, please contact them again so they know you’re safe.
If worried about loved ones overseas in areas affected by #HurricaneIrma, contact @StateDept at 1-888-407-4747 or IrmaEmergencyUSC@state.gov
If overseas and need help after #HurricaneIrma, call the @StateDept at 1-888-407-4747 or  email IrmaEmergencyUSC@state.gov.
#NeverForget the lives lost on 9/11, the heroism of our first responders & every day Americans who stood steadfast in the face of evil.
Helpful information from @DaVita – dialysis patients in need call 1-800-400-8331, regardless of where you normally receive treatment.
For @Aetna members using mail-order pharmacy, you can get a prescription at an alternative delivery location or refill lost prescriptions.
To file a damage claim through #NFIP call your agent directly. If you need help finding your carrier call 1-800-621-FEMA (3362) and select 2
Senior citizens in need of assistance should call FL Dept of Elder Affairs at 1-800-96-ELDER (1-800-963-5337)
The Florida Emergency Information Line is still open – call 1-800-342-3557 @FLSERT
To reach @FEMA Disaster Assistance call 1-800-621-FEMA (1-800-621-3362)
.@Allstate customers with #HurricanIrma claim-related inquiries can call 1-800-54-STORM for assistance.
Stay clear of downed power lines and report them and any outages to your power company immediately.
From @PinellasEM: As of 8:30pm, @SheriffPinellas deputies are coming off the road b/c safety issues w/sustained 40mph winds. #HurricaneIrma
If you're not in an evacuation zone, please shelter in place until storm passes and let family and friends know your location.
Important @fema note: If sheltering in a high-rise stay on floors just above flood water or storm surge. Stay in hallways or interior rooms.
Turn refrigerator/freezer to coldest setting & only open when necessary. Keep thermometer in refrigerator to ensure food is safe to eat.
Close storm shutters and stay away from windows. Flying glass from broken windows can cause severe injuries.
Fully charge your cell phone now so you will have a full battery in case you lose power. It'll be a vital resource after the storm.
Please bring loose, lightweight objects (projectiles) inside, anchor objects unsafe to bring inside (propane tanks), & cover your windows
Review evacuation plan with your family. Hurricanes are unpredictable & a small change in surge levels in Pinellas makes a big difference
Make a plan on how to get in touch with loved ones if you lose power. Texting is usually more reliable & faster than calling for hurricanes
For your emergency kit, you'll need enough food/water for at least three days, a flashlight, batteries, cash, medications, and first aid kit
Use our local tv and radio stations to keep updated on the weather and new emergency instructions, including any new evacuation orders
Contact VA’s Health Resource Center Disaster Hotline 1-800-507-4571 regarding health service and benefit inquiries during the storm period.
If a VA patient is displaced or has lost medications, contact the Heritage Health Customer Care Line at 1-866-265-0124, option 1
U.S. citizens abroad affected by #HurricaneIrma who require emergency assistance can contact the @StateDept via website, email & phone.
.@SheriffPinellas Gualtieri is right: these orders mean it's time to leave NOW, not later. #HurricaneIrma is a serious storm. @PinellasEM
Helpful #HurricaneIrma info from @UnitedWay: Call 211 for NON-EMERGENCY assistance or text zip code to 898-211 to connect with a specialist
To report suspected cases of price gouging during #HurricaneIrma, call the Florida Price Gouging Hotline at 1-866-9-NO-SCAM (1-866-966-7226)
.@PinellasEM Citizen Information Line remains open - call (727) 464-4333 #HurricaneIrma
The @FLSERT Emergency Information Line is open 24/7 – call 1-800-342-3557 #HurricaneIrma
To reach @FEMA Disaster Assistance call 1-800-621-FEMA (1-800-621-3362) #HurricaneIrma
Text FLPREPARES to 888777 to receive text alerts from @FLSERT/ FL Division of Emergency Mgmt during #HurricaneIrma
STORM SURGE WATCH FOR PINELLAS. Forecast drifting west. Talk to neighbors who don't have internet. The water WILL rise. Heed evac orders.
Hurricane Watch=conditions possible next 48 hrs. Review evacuation route & shelter info. at 727-453-3150 from landline. Review disaster kit.
Florida's price gouging hotline has been activated, make a report by calling 1-866-9-NO-SCAM. #HurricaneIrma
Make sure you have a family emergency communication plan! Designate an out-of-area contact person & meet up point in event of separation.
From @fema - you need: food & water for 3 days, battery powered radio, flashlight, cash, meds, 1st aid kit & important family docs. #Irma
American @LungAssociation has shared resources for those with lung diseases like COPD & asthma call 1-800-LUNG-USA.
